  "text": "Initially, linear regression lines were used to predict METs from the counts per minute for activities where the CV was Յ10 and activities where the CV was Ͼ10. Further examination of the data revealed that a linear regression did not yield the best fit. For example, the linear regression for activities where the CV is Յ10 significantly underestimated walking at 2 mph as well as running speeds Ͼ7 mph. Therefore, we chose an exponential curve for activities where the CV was Յ 10 (Fig. 2) . To verify the use of an exponential curve, we plotted the mean counts per minute vs. METs during treadmill walking and running from the study of King et al. [CITATION_1] in Fig. 2 .",
